The Government's Decisions:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Md. Palshi (Khurd) Ta. The scheme of Khamgaon Tap Water Supply Scheme has received an increase in the price of the scheme on account of acceptance of additional tender rates, increase in the rate of Goods and Services Tax (551) and technical changes subject to the following conditions: Rs. The revised price of 1,61,90, 400 / - (Rupees One Crore Sixty One Lakh Ninety Four Thousand Only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Suprama-2024 / Q. No.2 / Papu 9307 010 20.760189)
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval as well as the original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Gramin Pani Purabtha Division, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for the implementation of the scheme, maintenance, repairs (subject to special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or renovation of machinery to meet the recurring expenditure incurred every year.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) According to a 2013 report for €57, 21% of the state's water supply schemes lack this maintenance repair, resulting in poor maintenance / nonpayment of electricity of bills (F] VS Staeard. In fact, in order to make the scheme financially viable, the responsibility of increasing the water table rate as per requirement will lie with the concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.
